{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GreenNode","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Lang","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":"> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Lang","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","text":"SyntaxLanguage","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11CambiumCore14SyntaxLanguageP"}]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GreenNode"},{"type":"text","text":" is the position-independent representation of a syntactic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"production. It carries a kind, a flat array of children (other nodes and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tokens), the total UTF-8 byte length of all descendant text, and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pre-computed structural hash. Like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenToken","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", green nodes are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"shared"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" across positions and across tree versions: the same green"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"node may appear at many source positions when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GreenNodeCache"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dedupes equal candidates."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Construction","level":2,"text":"Construction"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most code never builds nodes directly — use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":", which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"routes through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GreenNodeCache"},{"type":"text","text":" for dedup and validates open\/close"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pairing. Direct construction is reserved for replacement and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out-of-band tree assembly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(kind:children:)"},{"type":"text","text":" (raw or typed kind) computes text length,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"counts node children, and builds the structural hash. It throws"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenStorageError\/textLengthOverflow","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if the children’s combined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text length would exceed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UInt32.max"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Children","level":2,"text":"Children"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Children appear in source order. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNode\/childCount","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" returns the total number"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of children (nodes plus tokens); "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNode\/nodeChildCount","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" returns just the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"node count, which is the metric the lazy red layer cares about. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNode\/child(at:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for indexed access and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNode\/childrenArray()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"materialize the full child list (allocates)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Identity","level":2,"text":"Identity"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNode\/identity","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" returns a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumCore\/GreenNodeIdentity","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" keyed on storage object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identity. Two nodes with equal "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":" share the same in-memory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"storage; two nodes that are structurally equal but allocated separately"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have distinct "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identity"},{"type":"text","text":". Identity is the right comparison for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"detecting structural sharing across tree versions; equality ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":") is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the right comparison for cache lookup."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Sendability","level":2,"text":"Sendability"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Green nodes are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@unchecked Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" because their storage is a final"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference type with immutable contents. They can be safely shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"across actor boundari